docs.text: slavery is bad .

docs.text: after hundreds of years , we've finally figured that one out .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this almost universal belief is the both the strength and weakness of director steven spielberg's latest " serious " film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: during the late 1830s , a portuguese slave ship carries a cargo of black men and women kidnapped from their home on africa's west coast to cuba to be sold into slavery .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: fifty-three of them are stuffed into the " la amistad " ( from a spanish word for " friendship " ) by their new spanish owners .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: freeing himself from his chains , senge pieh ( djimon hounsou ) , renamed cinque by his masters , leads a bloody revolt .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: after killing most of the crew , the africans force the remaining sailors to return them to their home - or so they think .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: instead the ship heads up the coast to the united states .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the amistad is boarded by an american naval ship and the revolutionaries are put on trial in connecticut for murder and piracy .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the legal question becomes are they free men fighting justly for their freedom or are they property .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if they are property , who do they belong to ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: their masters ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the spanish government ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: salvage rights of the officers who captured the ship ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the us government ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the defendants are pawns in several games .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: abolitionists theodore joadson ( morgan freeman ) and lewis tappan ( stellan skarsgard ) want to free them , but tappan sees them primarily as a means to further the cause .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: their lawyer roger baldwin ( matthew mcconaughey ) views the case as a simple one of property rights and a chance to make his share of legal fees .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: south carolina senator john c . calhoun ( arliss howard ) pursues the case for the political advancement of the southern states .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: president martin van buren ( nigel hawthorne ) is willing to force the result towards his own political ends .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when the verdict looks to free the africans , van buren replaces the judge with one more sympathetic to his wishes .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even that doesn't work and the new judge frees the kidnap victims .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: at the urging of calhoun , the president then appeals the case to the supreme court , populated by a majority of slave-owners .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this little-known ( try finding it in any history text book ) incident from america's past would have gone down a darker path were it not for former president john quincy adams ( anthony hopkins ) who is persuaded to argue the case before the supreme court .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the slavery issue is easy pickin's for spielberg .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: much like his " shindler's list " ( which followed " jurassic park " as this follows " lost world " ) , the moral sides are not difficult ones to choose .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: nazis and slave traders : both treat groups of others as less than human .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's not hard to see who the bad guys are .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: without that question to ponder , the director's job is more difficult .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he has to make the story interesting .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: spielberg succeeds for the most part .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the visual aspect of the film is beyond reproach .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: where the movie falls down is a bit more subtle .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are very few _people_ in the tale .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in fact , cinque is the only character who is fleshed out .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: tappan and joadson are " abolitionists " : symbols but not humans .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: van buren is a weak politician but nothing else .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the rest of the " slaves " barely exist other than dressing for the set .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: like many other films about people of color , almost all the major players are white .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the film's salvation lies in the acting strength of everyone involved and the powerful presence of hounsou .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the former model's first major role is a winner .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: without speaking more than five words of english , he conveys more emotion than most actors with a thousand lines of dialog .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the other stand-out is hopkins who seems to be making a career out of portraying american presidents ( he also played the title role in " nixon " ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the impassioned speech by the doddering old man who phases in and out of rationality is among the best court-room drama ever on the screen .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are some other great moments .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: especially impressive are the african's struggle to understand what is going on in the strange land .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: their interpretation of the bible based solely on the pictures and their own experiences is poignant .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as grand as the epic is , it would have more impact had it focused more on the experience from the point of view of the africans .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: more humanity in the fight for humanity would have made it a four-star film .
